  "body": "### Description\n\n*Type*: Feature\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I want to delete my chat only once on one device instead of deleting it on several devices.\n\n### Description\n\n*Summary*: as the continuation of #6697. \nCurrently, when you delete any chat or clearing chat history on one device, you still will need to repeat it on another device regardless sync is enabled or not.\n\n#### Expected behavior\nChat A is deleted;\nHistory for chat B is empty;\n\n#### Actual behavior\nchats are not changed\n\n### Reproduction\n*Prerequisites:* the same account is using on Device1 and Device2, sync is enabled between 2 devices (instructions are here https://ethstatus.testrail.net/index.php?/cases/view/5680).\nChats A and B (1-1 or group) are active on both devices and contain some history.\n\n- Open Status on Device1\n- Delete Chat A\n- Clear history for Chat B\n- Log in to Device2\n- Check chat A and B\n\n### Additional Information\n* Status version: nightly 20/11/2018\n* Operating System: all\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://static.testrail.io/5.6.0.3841/images/favicon.ico\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><strong><a href=\"https://ethstatus.testrail.net/index.php?/cases/view/5680\">Login - TestRail</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
